author: CBC News
title: Royals score 5 in the 7th inning to surge into Game 2 lead
text:
5 questions for the Blue Jays after Friday night's shutout loss 
Price, the star pitcher acquired from Detroit at this year's trade deadline, was brilliant early in the game but couldn't recover after the Royals started a rally on a 7th inning defensive miscue. 
The Royals, meanwhile, are hoping their strong bullpen can finish off the Blue Jays and give them a 2-0 lead in the best-of-seven battle for the American League. 
Game 2 of the American League Championship Series gets underway at 4 p.m. ET. Follow all of the action here on our live blog.
